  "en_notes_asad": [
    {
      "note_no": "76",
      "note": "Lit., \"has made us heirs to this land\", i.e., of paradise. According to all the classical commentators, the concept of \"heritage\" is used here metaphorically, to denote the rightful due, or portion, of the blessed. The term ard (lit., \"earth\" or \"land\") has also especially in poetry - the connotation of \"anything that is spread\" (cf. Lane 1, 48): hence my rendering of it, in the above context, as \"expanse\"."
    }
